# Forms with `useForm`

Use the project's custom `useForm` hook for every form. Do **not** add Formik, react-hook-form, or yup unless the project already uses them. Validation is schema-driven.

## Where the hook lives

`useForm` is a **shared** hook (not feature-scoped) — it lives in the top-level hooks folder and is reused by every feature's forms.

| Project type | Hook path | Import |
|---|---|---|
| **Single app** (default) | `src/hooks/useForm.tsx` | `import { useForm } from "@/hooks/useForm"` |
| **Monorepo** shared package | `packages/lib-utils/src/hooks/useForm.tsx` | `import { useForm } from "@repo/lib-utils/hooks/useForm"` (or your package name) |

A feature consumes it from inside `src/features/<feature>/components/...`:

```ts
import { useForm } from "@/hooks/useForm"; // shared hook
import type { LoginFormValues } from "@/features/auth/types/auth.types";
```

Install on a fresh project: `pnpm setup:useform` (see `.cursor/setup/hooks/README.md`). A worked example lives in `src/features/example/components/ExampleForm` (run `pnpm setup:example`).

Validators: `src/constants/form-validators.ts` (`is_required`, `get_prop_values`, `is_object`, `is_micro_field_required`).

## 1. Schema (`initialState`)

```ts
const initialState = {
  email:    { value: "", error: "", required: true, convertToLang: true },
  password: { value: "", error: "", required: true },
  remember: { value: false, error: "", required: false },
};
```

- `validator?: { func: (value, values) => boolean; error: string }` — when `func` returns `false`, `error` is shown. Use `convertToLang: true` when `error` is an i18n key.
- `type?: "boolean" | "TELEPHONE_WITH_EXT" | "NUMBER" | "PERCENTAGE_OBTAINED"` — special required checks.

## 2. Wire the hook

```ts
const submitHandler = (values: any, errors: any) => {
  if (errors) return;
  setLoading(true);
  authService.login(values)
    .then((res) => { /* success */ })
    .catch((err) => notifyError(err?.message))
    .finally(() => setLoading(false));
};

const { values, errors, dirty, disable, handleOnChange, handleOnSubmit, setUseFormStates } =
  useForm(initialState, submitHandler);
```

Submit callback: `(values | null, errors | null, extraParams?)`.

## 3. Bind fields

```tsx
<Input
  name="email"
  value={values?.email}
  onChange={handleOnChange}
  error={dirty?.email ? errors?.email : undefined}
  label={t(TITLES.FORMS.EMAIL)}
/>
<Button onClick={handleOnSubmit} disabled={loading || disable}>Submit</Button>
```

Show errors only when `dirty?.fieldName` is true.

## 4. Field handlers

| Handler | Use for |
|---|---|
| `handleOnChange` | text inputs |
| `handleOnNumberChange` | number inputs |
| `handleOnSelection` | single select |
| `handleOnMultipleSelection` | multi select |
| `handleOnValueChange` / `handleOnMultiselectChange` | custom controls |
| `handleOnCheckBoxChange` | boolean checkbox |
| `handleOnSwitch` | toggle |
| `handleOnFileUpload` | file upload |
| `handleOnRadioChange` | radio group |

Helpers: `setUseFormStates`, `setRequired`, `setValidator`, `validateSpecificFields`, `clearStateSchema`, `addUseFormFields`, `removeUseFormFields`.

## 5. Custom validation

Layer on `handleOnChange` + `setUseFormStates`, or put rules in the schema `validator`. Error strings must use i18n keys from `constants/titles.ts` / `constants/alerts.ts` (or your project's string constants).

## 6. Checklist

- [ ] Schema per field; `useForm(initialState, submitHandler)`.
- [ ] Correct handler + dirty-gated errors.
- [ ] Submit via `services/` (over `@/lib/fetch-client`, not raw fetch/axios in the component).
- [ ] No new form libraries introduced.
- [ ] Invoke `@useform-builder-agent` for full form implementation.
